After adding a service to your Application, you'll eventually need to manage the service. Managing can be creating data tables in a database or backup/restore your data.
For that use case we created the Cloud Foundry CLI Plugin Service Connector which is a local proxy app with that you will be able to connect to your service with you preferred local tools.

## <a id='installation-service-connector'></a> Install service connector
Windows:

install the newest version of the CLI (at least version 6.11.2 is required)
download the Swisscom Plugin into a folder (see url in the “Binaries” section below)
install the Swisscom Plugin into the CLI with the "cf install-plugin" command, e.g.: `cf install-plugin c:\downloads\swisscom-plugin.exe`


